[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(14) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Shalt thou not know it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "?—The second part of this prophecy (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:14-23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), describing the doom of Gog, is introduced (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:14-16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") with a repetition of the peaceful security of Israel, and of God’s leading against her this great foe in whose destruction He shall be magnified before all people. The whole passage becomes clearer by omitting the question and reading simply, “When Israel dwells securely thou wilt observe it and come,” &c.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:14-16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Ezekiel 38:14-16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "In that day, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — At that remarkable time, when I shall gather my people from their dispersions and bring them again to their own land, and they shall be established therein and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "dwell safely, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "without apprehension of danger from any enemy, and without any defence to prevent their being attacked; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "shalt thou not know it? — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Will they not be pointed out to thee as a people thou mayest easily conquer, and with whose spoils thou mayest without difficulty enrich thyself? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And thou shalt come from thy place out of the north parts — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thou and many people with thee, all of them riding upon horses, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — The character here given of this people may properly be applied to the Turks or Tartars, the strength of whose armies consists principally in their cavalry. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "As a cloud to cover the land ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— See on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "It shall be in the latter days — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This is repeated to prevent the application of the prophecy to any event that should take place before the days of the Messiah: see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 38:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And I will bring thee against my land — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I will permit thee to come; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that the heathen may know me, when I shall be sanctified in thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Shall be confessed to be a great God over all, a gracious and faithful God to my people, and a dreadful enemy and avenger against the wicked. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Before their eyes — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "In the sight of all the heathen that are with Gog, and much more in the sight of God’s own people. This signal victory over Gog and his associates shall be a means of bringing infidels to give glory to God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "38:14-23 The enemy should make a formidable descent upon the land of Israel. When Israel dwell safely under the Divine protection, shalt not thou be made to know it by finding that endeavours to destroy them are made in vain? Promises of security are treasured up in the word of God, against the troubles and dangers the church may be brought into in the latter days. In the destruction of sinners, God makes it appear that he is a great and holy God. We should desire and pray daily. Father, glorify thine own name.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "God will mark the prosperous security of the people, and rise up against them as an easy prey. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "14. shalt thou not know it?—to thy cost, being visited with punishment, while Israel dwells safely.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
